Ghana has lifted a ban placed on
three licensed cocoa-buying companies, including the local unit
of Armajaro, from operating in parts of the countryâ€™s biggest
growing region after allegations they were involved in
smuggling.  The companies have respected the ban, placed in April, and
had trained their staff on anti-smuggling, the Accra-based Ghana
Cocoa Board said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
